    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-09T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-09T09:00:00-05:00" n="1468"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1468">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.51/1521: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Patterson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-09T09:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 9, 1944—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 12:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>40. The Finance Minister<note n="29" xml:id="d1468fn29">Julio L. East.</note> has
                    informed Bondholders Protective Council responsive to their telegram of December
                    17 referred to in the Department’s instruction 2973, December 23, 1943,<note
                        n="30" xml:id="d1468fn30">
                        <ref target="frus1943v06#pg_757">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1943, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">vi</hi>, p. 757</ref>.</note> that he would <pb
                        facs="1583" n="1569" xml:id="pg_1569"/> be ready to begin conversations in
                    January. He has now completed the budget work and having received no notice from
                    the Council plans to be in the country for a rest between January 11 and 20th
                    unless Council intends to have a representative here during that time. If the
                    visit of the representative is scheduled for January 20 or thereafter a reply to
                    this message will not be necessary.</p>
                <p>The Minister indicated that no plan for the expected conversation had been made
                    but that the conversations themselves would be to develop basic proposals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Patterson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
